s on the continuing attempts to impose political unity on the peninsula.O'Callaghan divides his story into five compact historical periods and discusses political, social, economic, and cultural developments in each period. By treating states together, he is able to put into proper perspective the relationships among them, their similarities and differences, and the continuity of development from one period to the next. He gives proper attention to Spain's contacts with the rest of the medieval world, but his main concern is with the events and institutions on the peninsula itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aEurope. 4aHistory. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies.  aAlgarve.  aBlack Death.  aCatalonia.  aCatholicism.  aChristian and Islamic Spain.  aEuropean history.  aInquisition.  aIslamic Spain.  aMedieval Spain history.  aMedieval Spain studies.  aMedieval Spain.  aMuslims in the Iberian Peninsula.  aRoman Hispania.  acrusades history.  acrusades in medieval spain.  acrusades.  aeuropean history.  afall of caliphate spain.  afifth century spain.  ahispanic middle ages.  ahistory of spain.  aiberian peninsula history.  aislam in spain.  amedieval history introduction.  amedieval history.  amedieval iberia.  amedieval iberian peninsular history.  amedieval portuguese history.  amedieval spains.  amedieval spanish.  amedieval studies.  amedievalist.  amuslim portugal.  amuslims in spain.  aportuguese history.  aspain in the middle ages.  aspainish history.  aspanish history middle ages.  avisigoth era.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080146872840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801468728423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc